              <img src="https://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/goldbach_conjectures.png" alt="The weak twin primes conjecture states that there are infinitely many pairs of primes. The strong twin primes conjecture states that every prime p has a twin prime (p+2), although (p+2) may not look prime at first. The tautological prime conjecture states that the tautological prime conjecture is true." style="height: auto;" />
            </a>
            <p>The weak twin primes conjecture states that there are infinitely many pairs of primes. The strong twin primes conjecture states that every prime p has a twin prime (p+2), although (p+2) may not look prime at first. The tautological prime conjecture states that the tautological prime conjecture is true.</p>
            <p><a href="https://explainxkcd.com/1310/">Explanation</a></p>
